<h2 class="font-32 accent margin-top-60 sm-no-margin-top margin-bottom-20 mobile-text-center" ><strong>PERSON’S WITH INTELLECTUAL DEVELOPMENT DISABILITY (PwIDD)</strong></h2>
<p class="font-24 margin-vertical-20 font-italic" style="text-align:justify;">A person who is affected with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Down syndrome, Muscular Dystrophy, and Multiple Disability having low I.Q. are covered under PwIDDs. Their needs are same like anybody else. They have psychological needs, aspirations; emotional ups and downs and bonding with other peoples. These needs are first met at home and then in interactions with the society, be itthe friends, teachers, trainers or neighbors. Every parent wants to improve the life but they don’t know where to begin with. It is observed the PwIDDs perform well when they have family support. PwIDDs don’t need to show ‘pity’, they need ‘opportunity’ to enhance their abilities.</p>
<div class="margin-top-40 mobile-text-center"><a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-transparent" href="#">Learn More</a></div>
</div>
